						<summary>

						<p>Fragmentary stone bearing sculpture of Jina near the Kalamēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Khoṭṭiga.</p>						

						<p>This fragmentary record refers to Khoṭṭigadēva. Seems to commence with the praise of <hi rend="italic">Jina-śāsana.</hi> Mentions the king's subordinate of the Gaṅga family (name lost) bearing the titles <hi rend="italic">Satyavākya Koṅguṇivarma</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Dharmamahārāja.</hi> The characters belong to the 10th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
